Articles.Content:
Im interested in completeing some challenges but many challenges require a craft to be "Kerballed".

Can someone point me in the direction of a terminology page or explain to me what thet means?

I feel a bit silly if i keep missing it.

Any help would be appreciated, thanks much.

Edited October 24, 2015 by Gahooligan

Welcome aboard!

It means the vessel has a crew.

These two wiki pages could be helpful:

http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Abbreviations_and_acronyms

http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Terminology
Great links, Tex_NL. I've been struggling with a lot of that stuff, too.

okay, yeah...dur.

Kerballed...manned. I get it.

I didnt make the connection at first.

many thanks, also for the links as well.
